The 2019–20 San Francisco Dons men's basketball team represents the University of San Francisco during the 2019–20 NCAA Division I men's basketball season. The Dons, led by first-year head coach Todd Golden, play their home games at the War Memorial Gymnasium or the Chase Center as members of the West Coast Conference.


== Previous season ==
The Dons finished the 2018–19 season 21–10, 9–7 in WCC play to finish in fourth place. They lost in the Third Round to Pepperdine of the WCC Tournament. Despite having 21 wins and a better record they were not invited to a postseason tournament.On March 27, Kyle Smith left for San Francisco to accept the head coach position at Washington State. He finished with a five year record of 63–40 with two CBI appearances.  The Dons promoted assistant Todd Golden to head coaching position the following day.


